This paper primarily focuses on the security and analysis of Android cryptocurrency mining applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). However, the paper also involves machine learning-based detection, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) or information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of the most popular libraries and APIs used in mining app development could also fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or cryptography and security (cs.CY).
